ğŸ”¹ Why array size is fixed?
Because memory is allocated at compile time (or creation time) as a continuous block.
Resizing requires:
Creating new array
Copying elements
Thatâ€™s why size is fixed.

ğŸ”¹ Difference Between Array and ArrayList?
Array	                    ArrayList
Fixed size	              Dynamic size
Faster	                  Slightly slower
Stores primitives       	Stores objects only
No built-in methods	      Many utility methods
ArrayList internally uses an array and resizes when needed.

