ğŸ”¹ Why Arrays Are Faster Than Collections?
Because:
No resizing
No wrapper objects (for primitives)
Direct memory access
Less overhead

Collections add abstraction + resizing + object boxing.

âœ… 5ï¸âƒ£ THINKING QUESTION
â“ Why Binary Search Cannot Work on Unsorted Array?
Because binary search eliminates half of the array based on comparison.
Example:
Sorted:[2, 5, 8, 12, 20]
If target < mid â†’ go left.
But in unsorted:[12, 2, 20, 5, 8] You cannot decide:
Should I go left?
Should I go right?
Because order is not guaranteed.

ğŸ¯ Interview One-Line Answer:
Binary search depends on sorted order to eliminate half of the search space. Without order, we cannot safely discard half.
